Yahoo Fantasy OAuth Setup

Follow these steps to connect your Yahoo Fantasy leagues

Prerequisites: You need a Yahoo account and at least one fantasy football league to import teams.
1
Register Your App with Yahoo
Create a Yahoo App to get OAuth credentials

Visit the Yahoo Developer Portal and create a new app:

App Configuration:

  • â€¢ App Name: HalGrid Fantasy (or your choice)
  • â€¢ App Type: Web Application
  • â€¢ Redirect URI:http://localhost:3000/api/auth/yahoo/callback
  • â€¢ API Permissions: Fantasy Sports (Read)
2
Copy Your OAuth Credentials
Get your Client ID and Client Secret from Yahoo

After creating your app, Yahoo will provide:

Client ID- Public identifier for your app
Client Secret- Private key (keep secure!)
Never share your Client Secret publicly or commit it to version control!
3
Update Your Environment Variables
Add credentials to your .env.local file
.env.local
NEXT_PUBLIC_YAHOO_CLIENT_ID=your_yahoo_client_id_here
YAHOO_CLIENT_SECRET=your_yahoo_client_secret_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
Replace your_yahoo_client_id_here and your_yahoo_client_secret_here with your actual Yahoo credentials.
4
Restart Your Development Server
Apply the new environment variables

Stop your server (Ctrl+C) and restart it:

npm run dev
